	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Two good sources of more complete tailoring info are eq.stomped.com and eqtraders.com. That being said...<BR>
<BR>
buy a sewing kit (I suggest getting the Deluxe size right off the bat)<BR>
Combine 2 spiderling silk to make silk thread.<BR>
Combine 2 threads to make a bandage OR<BR>
combine 3 threads to make a silk cord, which is used in making 10% weight reducing bags (cord + LQ pelt).<BR>
Combine 2 spider silks (from large or giant spiders) to make a silk swatch.<BR>
<BR>
In response to the poster who asked about the weightless backpacks, sorry, all the tailored bags (and the backpack) are only 10% weight reduction. They're still great as they're also 10 slot instead of 8. The recipe is HQ Bear pelt + backpack pattern and is trivial at skill level 88. Save those HQ bear pelts!<BR>
<BR>
There are probably many cities where the backpack pattern is available but it is definately in Kelethin and Firiona Vie. I believe Firiona Vie might be the only city that has carries ALL patterns. Low level &quot;good race&quot; players are safe in the city if you want to stock up in one stop.<BR>
<BR>
This is just the tip of the iceberg, try those sites.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
