	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				OK, I want to suggest that you DO NOT waste practice points on tailoring.  You can get your skill level up to 10 for free.  Just make silk swatches.  I started making silk strings for my fishing flies (I made 1 stack of (20) silk string) and then I started making silk swatches when I decided I needed large bags and quivers.  On my tenth or so swatch I got a skill increase in tailoring (1).  By the time I finished my second stack I had a skill of 10.  This saved me practice points and money because both silk strings (combining 2 spiderling silks taken from widow hatchlings of GFay) and silk swatches (2 spider silks taken from giant dune tarantulas of Oasis) are free plus you get experience if you start early enough so you have to hunt them anyway.  Just a suggestion.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
