	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I started a DE SK and had never done tailoring with my other characters.  I first thought about it when I was killing spiderlings and getting the spiderling silk which is not stackable, I remembered that a friend had said that if you combine 2 in a sewing kit you will get 1 peice of silk thread which was stackable.  I bought a sewing kit and started collecting the silk items.  I was able to get EXP on the kill and skill went up to 15 by doing this.  You should put one point into tailoring to make it a little easier.  I would not recommend dropping more than one (valuable) training point because you can instead get it realativly easy in the Nekulos forest by combining Spider silk and Spiderling silks to make Silk Swatches and Silk Thread both of which are stackable and I never failed at them once.  After that I went to tattered gordets by using Ruined Bear Pelts and a gordet patterns.  I am at about 25 skill(not sure exactly) and havn't used more than one training point or spend more that about 5pp on gordet patterns and the sewing kit.  This skill can be profitable at a higher lvl with the sale of tailored backpacks, I will get there one day,hehe.  I hope this helps everyone.
				</font>
			</td>

